    <item>
      <title>Caroline&amp;#039;s Birthday - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 18 Jul 2025 02:44:47 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8254" class="post-8254 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Caroline&amp;#8217;s Birthday&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Tuesday (July 15th) was Caroline&amp;#8217;s birthday, so I headed over to her party. But she seemed surprised to see me, and she didn&amp;#8217;t even remember inviting me! Yikes, that made me feel unwanted. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/Array" alt="Caroline: Oh! Did I send you an invitation, bunny? I can't remember..." class="wp-image-8255" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I gave her a rock guitar for her gift, and she seemed to enjoy it. But then again, she said she would&amp;#8217;ve been just as happy with my belly button lint. Gross. 🤢&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/Array" alt="Caroline: Of course, you could have given me bellybutton lint, and I'd still treasure it." class="wp-image-8256" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She then gave me a glow clock in exchange for the &lt;s&gt;belly button lint&lt;/s&gt; rock guitar. Curt was also at the party, talking about how it must be nice to be young&amp;#8230;and then he said &amp;#8220;fuzzball.&amp;#8221; But that&amp;#8217;s just his catchphrase, and he&amp;#8217;s not specifically referring to the &lt;em&gt;fuzzy ball &lt;/em&gt;of belly button lint that Caroline wanted. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/Array" alt="Curt: Well, it must be nice to be young, fuzzball!" class="wp-image-8264" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The next day, it was raining in town. Whitney got her outfit wet, and she said it was traumatizing.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/Array" alt="Whitney: I got my new outfit all wet! Ugh! The whole ordeal was terribly traumatizing..." class="wp-image-8258" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Robin realized that she was ten minutes late for the reapplication of her lipstick. Does she apply it to her beak? Because birds don&amp;#8217;t have lips. 🤔&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/Array" alt="Robin: It's 6 o'clock already!? I was supposed to reapply my lipstick ten minutes ago!" class="wp-image-8260" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Pippy was at home, so I got to see the inside of her house now that she has unpacked. But it looks more like her back yard than the interior of a house. Still, I took a quick nap on her hammock.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/Array" alt="Taking a nap on Pippy's hammock inside her house." class="wp-image-8259" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, Drift told me to get ready to rock&amp;#8230;in a very rocky way. 🪨&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/Array" alt="Drift: Get ready to rock, 'cause when I rock, even rocks have to rock, in a pond!" class="wp-image-8262" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He thought that expression was &amp;#8220;rad enough&amp;#8221; to be the catchphrase of the year. But I thought his&lt;em&gt; repetitive remarks and repeated &amp;#8220;rocks&amp;#8221; render it remarkably redundant.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Curt was sick with a cold today, so I gave him a dose of medicine.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I visited Caroline, she was (somehow) able to see that I&amp;#8217;ve collected every type of bug. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/Array" alt="Caroline: OK, let's just take a look... Wow!! A full set? Already? You've caught every insect?" class="wp-image-8265" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She was amazed and impressed. I know I&amp;#8217;ve seen this dialogue before from other characters, but it&amp;#8217;s such a cute reaction for villagers to have. 😊&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/Array" alt="Caroline: That's amazing, bunny! I am so impressed right now, stop it!" class="wp-image-8263" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Whitney was packed up and ready to move out of town, but I was able to talk her of it. Un&lt;em&gt;pack&lt;/em&gt; your boxes, wolf girl!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Look for the next video episode coming in the next couple days!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/17/carolines-birthday/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-17T22:44:47-04:00"&gt;July 17, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-17T22:47:22-04:00"&gt;July 17, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/caroline-invitation.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Fang-Tastic Lineup - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/12/fang-tastic-lineup/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/12/fang-tastic-lineup/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 13 Jul 2025 03:59:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13501" class="post-13501 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Fang-Tastic Lineup&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Pascal was in town Wednesday, so I gave him a scallop. After wondering where pepper comes from (since salt comes from the ocean), he jumped into the river.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/12/fang-tastic-lineup/Array" alt="Pascal jumped into the river." class="wp-image-13502" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I followed him to the waterfall and watched him go over the falls.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/12/fang-tastic-lineup/Array" alt="Pascal goes over the waterfall in Animal Crossing: City Folk." class="wp-image-13503" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Moments later, I spotted a new house in town. Robin&amp;#8217;s replacement has moved in, and it&amp;#8217;s none other than Fang the wolf! Pretty cool!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/12/fang-tastic-lineup/Array" alt="Fang: Wait a minute, who are you? Were you in one of these boxes? Oh, you live in this town?" class="wp-image-13504" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;This town has actually become quite a good collection of villagers. I currently have Biskit, Marina, Fang, Big Top, Rosie, Nana, Mint, Antonio, Felicity, and Monty. Those last two may be mid, but I like everyone else. And there&amp;#8217;s nobody that I strongly dislike. Can&amp;#8217;t complain about this lineup!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Felicity told me she&amp;#8217;s not into bugs in general, but she does love the cute bugs! I&amp;#8217;m not sure which ones those would be, though.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="499" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/12/fang-tastic-lineup/Array" alt="Felicity: I'm out here catching bugs to complete my field guide of totally cute insects." class="wp-image-13505" sizes="auto, (max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I later had an 80-minute bug-hunting session, and I&amp;#8217;ve since posted a gameplay video of that session. If you&amp;#8217;d like, you can watch that on Youtube.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="Animal Crossing: City Folk - 80 min. Bug Hunt Gameplay Session 2025 (ACCF)" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/EFnEZqWVqjg?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I played again today, and a dog without eyes met me at the top of the ramp, telling me he was waiting for to come outside!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="499" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/12/fang-tastic-lineup/Array" alt="Biskit: I was waiting for you to come outside and play, dumbbell!" class="wp-image-13506" sizes="auto, (max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It almost sounds a bit threatening if you don&amp;#8217;t know Biskit. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Over by the museum, Monty gave me a free pep squad shirt. I didn&amp;#8217;t necessarily want it, but I can always sell it.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="499" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/12/fang-tastic-lineup/Array" alt="Monty: Feel free to do whatever you want with it, it's poop." class="wp-image-13507" sizes="auto, (max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Down at the Roost, I asked K.K. Slider for a random song. He performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Rally&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/12/fang-tastic-lineup/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Rally." class="wp-image-13508" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Marina has been sick with a cold this week, so I gave her some medicine Wednesday and today. Get well soon, Marina!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While I didn&amp;#8217;t specifically go on a bug hunt tonight, I did manage (somehow) to catch two tarantulas and an arapaima within 60 seconds!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And right before I wrapped up my game, Big Top asked me for a new catchphrase. I told him to say &amp;#8220;528 bells,&amp;#8221; which may eventually pay off. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="499" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/12/fang-tastic-lineup/Array" alt="Big Top: Thanks for the rockin' catchphrase, 528 bells!" class="wp-image-13509" sizes="auto, (max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;For those who don&amp;#8217;t know, 528 bells is a common reward for completing a favor for a villager. So stay tuned!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/12/fang-tastic-lineup/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-12T23:59:00-04:00"&gt;July 12, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-13T01:19:57-04:00"&gt;July 13, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/RUU_8284-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Bob&amp;#039;s Cobbler Dream - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/12/bobs-cobbler-dream/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/12/bobs-cobbler-dream/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 13 Jul 2025 02:53:26 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8862" class="post-8862 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Bob&amp;#8217;s Cobbler Dream&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Wednesday (July 9th) was Static&amp;#8217;s birthday. For his gift, I gave him a throwback race-car bed that I purchased at Nook&amp;#8217;s Cranny.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/12/bobs-cobbler-dream/Array" alt="Static: A throwback race-car bed? This is one mighty generous gift!" class="wp-image-8863" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Even though Static attended the birthday of fellow squirrel Agent S last week, Agent S did not return the favor. Instead, Ankha was Static&amp;#8217;s other party attendee. And she was giving mixed messages about how much she was enjoying it. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/12/bobs-cobbler-dream/Array" alt="Ankha: I LOVE celebrating birthdays, don't you, I hate it?" class="wp-image-8864" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Thursday, Merengue was talking about moving out of town. But of course, I made her change her mind.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/12/bobs-cobbler-dream/Array" alt="Merengue: Honestly, the idea of leaving here was making me sad. I'm glad you convinced me to stay, in a pie." class="wp-image-8865" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;In a pie, where you belong. 🍰&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The summer fishing tournament was held today, and I found three of my villagers all huddled up and fishing in the same spot: Ankha, Bob, and Merengue.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="400" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/12/bobs-cobbler-dream/Array" alt="Merengue, Bob, and Ankha fishing together during the tournament." class="wp-image-8866" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Maybe they should space out a bit. Bob told me that it was a great day for fishing, because the water was wet and the sky is up. Classic Bob logic. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/12/bobs-cobbler-dream/Array" alt="Bob: It's a great day for fishing! The water is wet and the sky is up! A huh huh huh..." class="wp-image-8867" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I participated in one run of the tourney, and I caught seven fish in the three-minute time limit, including two red snappers.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/12/bobs-cobbler-dream/Array" alt="Catching a 2nd red snapper during the fishing tournament." class="wp-image-8868" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;My seven fish earned me a score of nine points, and I sold the fish for a total of 12,375 bells. I then redeemed ten points for a fish print.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Later on, I found a scallop while diving. Pascal popped up to ask for it, and he told me that getting framed sounds like a good thing.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/12/bobs-cobbler-dream/Array" alt="Pascal: Getting framed sounds like it oughta be a good thing. Like they're hangin' your photo up in the hall of fame." class="wp-image-8869" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He gave me a pearl for the scallop.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I listened in on a conversation between my purple friends, Static and Bob. Static asked Bob about his future plans for when he grows up. Bob replied that he dreamed of building a house made out of peach cobbler!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/12/bobs-cobbler-dream/Array" alt="Bob: I wanna build a great big house made out of peach cobbler!" class="wp-image-8870" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Bob the Builder?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Static wasn&amp;#8217;t on board.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/12/bobs-cobbler-dream/Array" alt="Static: What kinda cockamamie dream is that? Talkin' to you wears me out..." class="wp-image-8871" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Sunday, a sick Bob gave me a jinbei after I gave him some medicine.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Wisp gave me a purple camo wall after I gathered up his spirits for him.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;On Tuesday, I sold 13 fish to C.J. for 198,000 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Flick was in town Wednesday, and I sold him 17 bugs for 111,000 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I helped Gulliver yesterday, and he sent me a veil in the mail.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;See you next time!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/12/bobs-cobbler-dream/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-12T22:53:26-04:00"&gt;July 12, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-12T22:55:10-04:00"&gt;July 12, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/static-racecar-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Cake Debate - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 12 Jul 2025 03:55:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8243" class="post-8243 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Cake Debate&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Robin told me that she&amp;#8217;s happiest when she can relax in her own home&amp;#8230;on a pizza.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Robin: I'm at my happiest when I can relax in the comfort of my own home...on a pizza." class="wp-image-8244" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I&amp;#8230;almost&amp;#8230;agree.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Filbert asked me to deliver a letter to Truffles, because he doesn&amp;#8217;t trust the post office to get it to the right person.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Filbert: I'd be so embarrassed, my head would probably burst into flames, bucko!" class="wp-image-8245" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Even though Filbert didn&amp;#8217;t want anyone other than Truffles to read it, Truffles was eager to read it with me. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Truffles: Hey, bunny, let's read it together, on my Wii!" class="wp-image-8246" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In the letter, Filbert admitted to eating a 20-pound cherry delight. When I told him the delivery was done, he rewarded me with a stone wall.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I listened in on a conversation: Caroline asked Truffles what kind of cake she would be, if she could be a cake. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Caroline: Hey, Truffles. If you could be any cake in the world, what would you be?" class="wp-image-8247" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Truffles already knew the answer. She&amp;#8217;d be a carrot cake. 🥕&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Truffles: Oh, that's easy. Carrot. What, did you think I wasn't going to have an answer?" class="wp-image-8248" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Truffles said she thinks about this all the time, and she said she&amp;#8217;d have a delicious frosting hat.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Truffles: Dude, I think about this ALL THE TIME. I'd have a delicious frosting hat." class="wp-image-8249" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Caroline said that she might be a cheesecake because she likes cheese, but she hasn&amp;#8217;t put much thought into it. Truffles scolded her for not planning for situations like this. This game is so crazy sometimes.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Truffles: Oh, Caroline, this isn't the sort of thing you can leave to chance..." class="wp-image-8250" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, Tank&amp;#8217;s replacement moved in. Say hello to Pippy the rabbit.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Pippy: Evening! I'm Pippy. I gotta say, I just love to walk around." class="wp-image-8251" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I kind of like her, but she&amp;#8217;s definitely not one of my favorites. It&amp;#8217;s funny though, how villagers can remind you of people (former friends, for example) that really liked that villager.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Even though I do extended bug-catching sessions in Wild World like I do in &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EFnEZqWVqjg" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"&gt;City Folk&lt;/a&gt;, I did catch a couple of elephant beetles tonight.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="I caught an elephant beetle! The heavyweight of beetles!" class="wp-image-8252" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Have a good weekend, everyone! And good luck with your summer bug hunting, if you&amp;#8217;re into that. 🪲&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-11T23:55:00-04:00"&gt;July 11, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-12T00:25:07-04:00"&gt;July 12, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/robin-pizza3.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Sustainable Forest Fires - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Jul 2025 03:57:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13490" class="post-13490 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Sustainable Forest Fires&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, I received Robin&amp;#8217;s moving-out letter in the mail. She doesn&amp;#8217;t call it a goodbye, because she&amp;#8217;s sure we&amp;#8217;ll meet again somewhere. And that&amp;#8217;s probably more true than she knows, since she also lives in my Wild World town.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/Array" alt="To: Jeff, I've decided to move away from Forest. It's hard to say bye to good friends like you. So I won't. Because I'm SURE we'll meet again somewhere! -From: Robin" class="wp-image-13492" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;While nosing through Antonio&amp;#8217;s things, I got this curious message that said &amp;#8220;Let&amp;#8217;s just pretend we didn&amp;#8217;t see that&amp;#8230;&amp;#8221; Except that I could literally see that nothing was inside. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/Array" alt="...Let's just pretend we didn't see that, shall we?" class="wp-image-13493" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;What&amp;#8217;s in the box?&lt;br&gt;Nothing! Absolutely nothing!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Rosie approached me and gave me a free regal wall. She was on her way to throw it out, but she said it&amp;#8217;s better to recycle anyway.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/Array" alt="Rosie: I'm, like, totally concerned about greenhouse flashes and sustainable forest fires or whatever!" class="wp-image-13495" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;This sounds like Lindsay Bluth.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Later on, I held my first bug-catching session of the summer. I started shortly before 11 p.m., because I know more of the valuable bugs come out at 11:00. However, I was a bit disappointed when it suddenly started to rain right when the clock struck eleven! I wasn&amp;#8217;t sure which of the bugs the rain would prevent from appearing.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;However, I shouldn&amp;#8217;t have worried. I was seeing a lot of scarab beetles, and a good mix of the other regular summer bugs too. But the rain also had a positive side-effect: It allowed me to catch two coelacanths!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/Array" alt="A coelacanth?" class="wp-image-13494" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In slightly over an hour of bug-catching (and a little fishing too), I made about 250,000 bells.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, Nana sent me a letter telling me that she was over her cold. She sent me an office locker to say thanks for the medicine I&amp;#8217;ve been giving her lately.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I went over to the Roost to check out K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s Saturday night show, and he performed &amp;#8220;Comrade K.K.&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: Comrade K.K.." class="wp-image-13496" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Monty asked me for a new catchphrase, and I wanted him to say &amp;#8220;it&amp;#8217;s poop.&amp;#8221; However, the game wouldn&amp;#8217;t let me say that. So I added an extra &amp;#8220;o&amp;#8221; and then it worked out just fine. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/Array" alt="Monty: Wander around on a day like this one, and see what you discover, it's pooop." class="wp-image-13497" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;While I haven&amp;#8217;t yet recorded a bug hunting gameplay session video yet for 2025, I will be doing that soon&amp;#8230;perhaps by next week.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-05T23:57:00-04:00"&gt;July 5, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-06T02:32:39-04:00"&gt;July 6, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/RUU_8277-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Blue, Cornered, Multifaceted - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Jul 2025 03:44:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8853" class="post-8853 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Blue, Cornered, Multifaceted&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday, Quillson the duck was camping here in Forest for the 2nd time. I ducked out before he could inquire about moving in.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="Quillson, at the campsite: Hey, you're a local, right? The name's Quillson. Ha HA! That's how I laugh." class="wp-image-8855" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Louie sent me a letter with a blue corner attached. Since it was Agent S&amp;#8217;s birthday, I thought that would make a good gift for her. It is blue, after all. So I wrapped it up and headed to the squirrel superhero&amp;#8217;s party. But when I gave her the present, there was a problem: She said she already has a blue corner! Oops!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="Agent S: The thing is...I totes have a blue corner already." class="wp-image-8856" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;However, she still accepted it. Another squirrel, Static, was also at the party. And he even called himself &amp;#8220;an old cuss.&amp;#8221; 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="Static: Seein' someone have that much fun is enough to make even an old cuss like me smile! C'mon, let's celebrate!" class="wp-image-8857" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I listened in on a conversation between Agent S and Bones. Agent S said that her goal was to become a multifaceted pop star, and Bones didn&amp;#8217;t understand. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="Agent S: My goal is to be, you know, a multifaceted pop star." class="wp-image-8858" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="Bones: A munchy-fact-ed whatnow?" class="wp-image-8859" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, I had another camper at the campsite. It was Peggy the pig, but I have no interest in bringing home &lt;em&gt;this &lt;/em&gt;bacon.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="Peggy: Hi there! I'm Peggy, and I'm totes camping on your awesome island!" class="wp-image-8860" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;K.K. Slider was in town tonight for his Saturday night show, and I asked him for a random song. He performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Rally&amp;#8221; for me, Ankha, Bob, and Bones. Well, and a mosquito.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="K.K. Slider performs for Ankha, Bones, Bob, and Jeff." class="wp-image-8854" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Sunday, K.K. Slider performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Ballad&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;On Tuesday, I sold 18 fish to C.J. for a whopping 312,000 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;On Wednesday, Wisp gave me a garden chair when I returned his spirits to him.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Flick was in town, and I sold him 32 bugs for 159,000 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Yesterday, I returned a lost item to June. She rewarded me with some cat grass.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I helped out Gullivarrr, and he sent me another pirate outfit today.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-05T23:44:00-04:00"&gt;July 5, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-06T00:56:40-04:00"&gt;July 6, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
